                        "correctAnswerIndex": 0,
                        "correctFeedback": "Correct! Errors you raise can be caught with try/except.",
                        "incorrectFeedback": "Raised errors work exactly like built-in errors.",
                        "explanation": "All errors, whether built-in or raised by you, can be caught with try/except."
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "when_to_raise",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "**When to raise errors:**"
                },
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "content": "",
                    "properties": {
                        "numbered": false,
                        "items": [
                            "When input values are invalid",
                            "When operations can't be completed safely",
                            "When required conditions aren't met",
                            "To make your code fail fast with clear messages"
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Raising errors early prevents bigger problems later in your program."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "practical_example",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Let's see a complete example with validation."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "def create_user(name, age):\n    if not name:\n        raise ValueError(\"Name required\")\n    if age < 0:\n        raise ValueError(\"Invalid age\")\n    return {\"name\": name, \"age\": age}\n\ntry:\n    user = create_user(\"Bob\", 30)\n    print(f\"User: {user}\")\nexcept ValueError as e:\n    print(f\"Error: {e}\")",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "User: {'name': 'Bob', 'age': 30}"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "The function checks if `name` exists and if `age` is not negative. If any check fails, it raises a `ValueError`. The try/except block catches any raised errors."
                }
            ]
        },
